-- Uganda Police Arrest Rwandan Genocide Suspect Wanted in Belgium
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-07-06T08:08:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-06/uganda-police-arrest-rwandan-genocide-suspect-wanted-in-belgium.html
Uganda arrested a Rwandan wanted by a
Belgian court for suspected complicity in the 1994 genocide in
his country, the Daily Monitor Online reported, citing police.  Thaddee Kwitonda, 51, wanted since April 2011, was arrested
yesterday in Kampala, the capital, after police trailed him for
three months, the Kampala-based newspaper reported, citing
police spokesman Asuman Mugenyi. The suspect, who holds a
Belgian passport, arrived in Uganda in March, it said.  At least 800,000 people, mainly from the Tutsi minority,
were killed in the  Rwandan genocide , according to the  United
Nations .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
